[background arg="res://Bg/classroom.png" fade="1.0"]
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 4/C4S2/c4s2 Conrad sits at a desk.mp3" volume=25 bus="Voice"]
	Celestine sits at a desk, notes spread before your. Mark stands nearby.
	join Celestine (half) left
	join Mark (Mark_half) right
	Celestine: Let me review what we know.
	Celestine: Six students received notes. Each note references a specific moral failing or questionable decision.
	Mark: Ben witnessed cheating. Alice took credit for others' work. What about the others?
	Celestine: Ryan ignored bullying. Ria was dishonest with a friend. Two others made similar choices.
	Celestine: The pattern is clear - someone is identifying students who acted unethically and confronting them.
	Mark: But why? What's the endgame?
	Celestine: That's what bothers me. Is this punishment? Education? Some kind of social experiment?
	join "Diwata Laya" (Half) center
	[signal arg="laya_start"]
	"Diwata Laya" materializes, your expression thoughtful.
	"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]These notes carry intention, but not malice.[/color][/i]
	"Celestine (Thinking)": What do you sense?
	"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]Whoever writes them believes they are helping. Guiding.[/color][/i]
	"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]But their method lacks wisdom. They push without permission, judge without understanding.[/color][/i]
	"Celestine (Thinking)": So not an enemy, but not an ally either.
	"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]Someone who has learned about teaching, but not yet about compassion.[/color][/i]
	[signal arg="laya_end"]
	leave "Diwata Laya"
	Celestine: Laya's right. This feels like someone trying to imitate moral teaching but missing the point.
	Mark: Like they read a book about psychology and decided to play therapist?
	Celestine: Exactly.
	Celestine: We need to find the source. Who has access to this much information about students?
	Mark: Teachers? The counselor? Student council?
	Celestine: Or someone who observes very carefully. Someone who pays attention.
else:
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 4/C4S2/c4s2 Conrad sits at a desk.mp3" volume=25 bus="Voice"]
	Conrad sits at a desk, notes spread before you. Mark stands nearby.
	join Conrad (half) left
	join Mark (Mark_half) right
