	Mark: But why? What's the endgame?
	Conrad: That's what bothers me. Is this punishment? Education? Some kind of social experiment?
	join "Diwata Laya" (Half) center
	[signal arg="laya_start"]
	"Diwata Laya" materializes, your expression thoughtful.
	"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]These notes carry intention, but not malice.[/color][/i]
	"Conrad (Thinking)": What do you sense?
	"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]Whoever writes them believes they are helping. Guiding.[/color][/i]
	"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]But their method lacks wisdom. They push without permission, judge without understanding.[/color][/i]
	"Conrad (Thinking)": So not an enemy, but not an ally either.
	"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]Someone who has learned about teaching, but not yet about compassion.[/color][/i]
