	Conrad: Or someone who observes very carefully. Someone who pays attention.
The Principal enters the room.
join Principal (Principal_half) rightmost
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	Principal: Celestine. I'm glad you're looking into this.
	Principal: Parents are starting to call. Students feel targeted, watched.
	Principal: Do you have any leads?
	Celestine: I need to check the library. Some of these notes reference obscure psychological concepts.
	Celestine: Whoever is doing this has been studying moral philosophy and behavioral psychology.
	Principal: The library keeps records of book checkouts. I'll authorize your access.
	Celestine: Thank you. There's one more thing.
	Celestine: Has anyone asked about student records recently? Grades, behavior reports, anything like that?
	Principal: No. Those are strictly confidential. Even teachers can only access their own students.
	Celestine: Then our note-writer is gathering information another way. Observation, rumors, or...
	Mark: Or they found something. A resource we don't know about.
	Celestine: Let's check the library.
	leave Principal
	leave Celestine
	leave Mark
else:
	Principal: Conrad. I'm glad you're looking into this.
	Principal: Parents are starting to call. Students feel targeted, watched.
	Principal: Do you have any leads?
	Conrad: I need to check the library. Some of these notes reference obscure psychological concepts.
	Conrad: Whoever is doing this has been studying moral philosophy and behavioral psychology.
	Principal: The library keeps records of book checkouts. I'll authorize your access.
	Conrad: Thank you. There's one more thing.
	Conrad: Has anyone asked about student records recently? Grades, behavior reports, anything like that?
	Principal: No. Those are strictly confidential. Even teachers can only access their own students.
	Conrad: Then our note-writer is gathering information another way. Observation, rumors, or...
	Mark: Or they found something. A resource we don't know about.
	Conrad: Let's check the library.
	leave Principal
	leave Conrad
	leave Mark
[background arg="res://Bg/library.png" fade="1.0"]
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 4/C4S2/c4s2 the library is quiet.mp3" volume=25 bus="Voice"]
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	join Celestine (half) left
	join Mark (Mark_half) right
	The library is quiet. A few students study at tables.
	Celestine approaches the circulation desk.
	Celestine: Excuse me. I need to check recent book checkouts, particularly psychology and philosophy sections.
	The librarian pulls up records on your computer.
	Librarian: Let's see... several students have checked out ethics texts recently. That's not unusual.
	Librarian: But there is something odd. Someone accessed the restricted archive section twice last week.
	Celestine: The archive? Who has permission?
	Librarian: Faculty, seniors working on thesis projects, and special permission cases.
	Librarian: According to the log... it was Alex. She signed out for historical research.
	Mark: Alex? I know her. She's in our grade. Always studying, very serious.
	Celestine: What was she researching?
	Librarian: Her sign-in form said "educational history project for Advanced Studies class."
	Celestine: Can we access the archive?
	Librarian: With permission, yes. Let me get the key.
	join "Diwata Laya" (Half) center
	[signal arg="laya_start"]
	"Diwata Laya": Knowledge leads to understanding. Test yourself before proceeding.
	if {selected_subject} == "english":
		[signal arg="start_minigame dialogue_choice_approach_suspect"]
	elif {selected_subject} == "math":
		Celestine: Three students could be involved. Let me deduce their behavior patterns.
		Celestine: Using logical reasoning and conditional statements...
		Celestine: I can systematically match each student to their role.
		[signal arg="start_minigame logic_grid_suspect_behavior_math"]
	elif {selected_subject} == "science":
		if {selected_character} == "celestine":
			Celestine: The note distribution system worked like an electrical circuit.
			Celestine: Alex was the battery, the lockers were conductors, and students were resistors.
			Celestine: Let me match each component to its electrical role!
		else:
			Conrad: The note distribution system worked like an electrical circuit.
			Conrad: Alex was the battery, the lockers were conductors, and students were resistors.
			Conrad: Let me match each component to its electrical role!
		[signal arg="start_minigame logic_grid_information_circuit_science"]
	"Diwata Laya": Wisdom guides your judgment.
	[signal arg="laya_end"]
	leave "Diwata Laya"
	leave Celestine
	leave Mark
else:
	join Conrad (half) left
	join Mark (Mark_half) right
